You are debugging a high-performance C++ application that processes real-time financial market data. The application has been experiencing memory leaks that only appear after running for several hours under heavy load with multiple concurrent threads. Memory usage grows from 200MB to over 8GB, eventually causing system instability.

The application receives market data feeds, processes them through multiple worker threads, caches results, and serves data to clients. Below is the core processing code that contains several subtle but critical memory management bugs:

